      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "52983d845083013b",
      "text": "A wave of Cypherpunk and Internet related discourse within this arena was ignited by the furore surrounding Phil Zimmerman and the power of PGP (1991) to enable '[[Pretty Good Privacy]]'. This invoked existing discourse about the rights of citizens and the social contract. Amongst this backdrop, radical thinkers began to wonder which innovations would challenge the raison d'être of state and government. It included its instruments such as fiat currency, contracts, rights and market regulation."
